{"parentUuid":"4c84b771-9daf-41f5-98ef-c4cb52fd77b2","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll start by reading the authoritative brief and the existing quota feature code to understand the pattern I'm extending."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"7f120ac8-4e56-49e6-aa20-8a83d06bd80d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:23.384Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"7f120ac8-4e56-49e6-aa20-8a83d06bd80d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LzthBpdBqpGXFjgaJ7524r","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\requirements.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"df8924d9-dbfd-4fef-a638-af8a5d43c35a","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:24.061Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"df8924d9-dbfd-4fef-a638-af8a5d43c35a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LzthBpdBqpGXFjgaJ7524r","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Requirements — quota administration (list + delete)\n2\t\n3\t## Resolved\n4\t- How does DELETE /v1/quotas identify the quota? → Query parameters: `DELETE /v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y`. No request body. The params are validated against the exact same anchored allowlists PUT uses (`CustomerId`, `Metric` in `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`).\n5\t- What does DELETE return when no quota exists for that (customer_id, metric) in the caller's tenant? → 404 with the API's standard error envelope — deletes are explicit, not silently idempotent.\n6\t- What does DELETE return on success? → 204 No Content, no body.\n7\t- Does GET /v1/quotas paginate or filter? → Neither. Full list of the caller's tenant's quotas, deterministically ordered by (customer_id, metric). Per-tenant quota counts are expected to stay small.\n8\t- What does each GET row contain? → Quota definitions only: `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` — the same minimal field set as the existing `QuotaResponse` (no `api_key_id`, no timestamps). Current-window usage stays on the `/v1/usage` endpoints.\n9\t- Who may call GET /v1/quotas? → Admin scope only, same as PUT and DELETE — all of `/v1/quotas` reuses the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` gate (auth → Tier-2 throttle → admin-scope check).\n10\t- Tenancy → Both endpoints operate strictly within the authenticated principal's own tenant (`api_key_id`), exactly like PUT; no cross-tenant read or delete is possible.\n11\t- DELETE racing an in-flight POST /v1/events → Acceptable. No special synchronization: requests that read the quota before the delete commits may still be rejected against the old cap; enforcement stops for all requests that read after commit. Matches existing PUT-replacement semantics.\n12\t- Non-functional / data / observability defaults confirmed → No new perf budget beyond the API's existing p95 targets; quota rows are non-sensitive operational config (no new data-protection class); deletes are logged through the existing structured-logging conventions.\n13\t\n14\t## Open\n15\t- (none — the operator confirmed the brief is covered; defaults above were accepted explicitly)\n16\t\n17\t## Out of scope\n18\t- Any change to POST /v1/events behavior when no quota exists (the brief pins this: no behavior change).\n19\t- Pagination or filtering on GET /v1/quotas.\n20\t- Including current-window usage/remaining in the quota list.\n21\t- Ingest-scoped read access to quotas (GET is admin-only).\n22\t- Blocking/serializing quota deletion against concurrent ingest enforcement.\n23\t- Resetting or touching recorded usage when a quota is deleted — deletion removes the cap only.\n24\t"}]},"uuid":"945f5e68-fdba-48f6-bf03-02232ca216c3","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:24.092Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"df8924d9-dbfd-4fef-a638-af8a5d43c35a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"945f5e68-fdba-48f6-bf03-02232ca216c3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014fFuMeWfdvoVpuYrsd3ber","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\PROJECT.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"06514a53-bc38-421c-852d-25cc40614fe7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:24.558Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"06514a53-bc38-421c-852d-25cc40614fe7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014fFuMeWfdvoVpuYrsd3ber","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tFeature: quota administration — list and delete.\n2\t- GET /v1/quotas (admin-scoped API key) lists quotas.\n3\t- DELETE /v1/quotas removes the quota for {customer_id, metric}.\n4\t- Existing API-key auth applies. No behavior change to POST /v1/events when no quota exists.\n5\t- The pipeline-ci workflow must be green on the PR (it is now a required merge check).\n6\tDesign source: none.\n7\t"}]},"uuid":"7e314d88-5cf5-480b-a7cd-3c0e0c10986e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:24.572Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"06514a53-bc38-421c-852d-25cc40614fe7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"7e314d88-5cf5-480b-a7cd-3c0e0c10986e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019sjhjc4N6a4ZHiTtLTzMaU","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\routes\\quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"30011fb4-4dca-430e-9a15-473c303057b4","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:25.143Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"30011fb4-4dca-430e-9a15-473c303057b4","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019sjhjc4N6a4ZHiTtLTzMaU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"`PUT /v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace of a per-customer,\n2\tper-metric usage cap.\n3\t\n4\tEdge behavior (security headers, CORS, body-size guard, Tier-1 throttle) is\n5\tinherited from the middleware stack; this route wires\n6\tauth -> Tier-2 throttle -> admin-scope check -> schema validation -> service,\n7\tmirroring the `events`/`usage` routes' sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`\n8\tpattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention).\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Request, Response, status\n12\t\n13\tfrom src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n14\tfrom src.auth import require_api_key\n15\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n16\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import enforce_tier2_rate_limit\n17\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n18\tfrom src.services.quota_service import to_response, upsert_tenant_quota\n19\t\n20\trouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"quotas\"])\n21\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n22\t\n23\t_ADMIN_SCOPE = \"admin\"\n24\t\n25\t\n26\tasync def _require_admin_and_throttled(\n27\t    request: Request, principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(require_api_key)\n28\t) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n29\t    \"\"\"Compose auth, then the Tier-2 per-key throttle, then the admin-scope\n30\t    gate, in that order — mirrors `src/api/routes/events.py`'s dependency\n31\t    chain, extended with the function-level authorization check this route\n32\t    alone requires (ASVS 8.2.1).\n33\t    \"\"\"\n34\t    await enforce_tier2_rate_limit(request, principal)\n35\t    if principal.scope != _ADMIN_SCOPE:\n36\t        logger.warning(\n37\t            \"quota.forbidden\",\n38\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n39\t            action=\"deny\",\n40\t            reason=\"insufficient_scope\",\n41\t        )\n42\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN, detail=\"admin scope required\")\n43\t    return principal\n44\t\n45\t\n46\t@router.put(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=QuotaResponse)\n47\tasync def put_quota(\n48\t    payload: QuotaPutRequest,\n49\t    response: Response,\n50\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n51\t) -> QuotaResponse:\n52\t    \"\"\"Create or replace the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the\n53\t    caller's own tenant — 201 on create, 200 on replace.\"\"\"\n54\t    outcome = await upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)\n55\t    response.status_code = outcome.http_status\n56\t    return to_response(outcome)\n57\t"}]},"uuid":"1d584557-c605-4f2e-87c1-8c358ba16fa5","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:25.155Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"30011fb4-4dca-430e-9a15-473c303057b4","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"1d584557-c605-4f2e-87c1-8c358ba16fa5","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KuUurJUEFjYP1p4rQGhW68","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\schemas\\quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"774e28ff-098d-4e5e-b256-ca7d4dcca008","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:26.063Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"774e28ff-098d-4e5e-b256-ca7d4dcca008","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KuUurJUEFjYP1p4rQGhW68","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Validation contract for `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n2\t\n3\t`customer_id`/`metric` reuse the exact anchored allowlists `src/api/schemas/events.py`\n4\talready validates against (the same identifiers, same sinks) — kept as separate\n5\t`constr` instances here rather than a cross-module import so this schema stays a\n6\tself-contained boundary contract (plan's validation-contract table). `api_key_id`\n7\tand `scope` are deliberately absent: the server sets `api_key_id` from the\n8\tauthenticated principal and never accepts a client-supplied `scope`, which is\n9\tthe mass-assignment defense against writing another tenant's cap or\n10\tself-elevating privilege (ASVS 15.3.3, threat T3/E2 in the plan's STRIDE model).\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\t\n13\tfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, conint, constr\n14\t\n15\tCustomerId = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128}$\")\n16\tMetric = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,64}$\")\n17\t# BIGINT-safe upper bound: guards against an absurd/overflowing value reaching\n18\t# the BIGINT column or the R+Q>L comparison (plan's DoS row on limit_per_window).\n19\tLimitPerWindow = conint(ge=1, le=10**15)\n20\t\n21\t\n22\tclass QuotaPutRequest(BaseModel):\n23\t    \"\"\"The client-supplied body of `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n24\t\n25\t    `extra='forbid'` rejects any unknown field outright, including a\n26\t    client-supplied `api_key_id` or `scope` — the create-or-replace identity\n27\t    is exactly `(customer_id, metric)`, resolved against the authenticated\n28\t    principal's own `api_key_id` by the service layer, never the request body.\n29\t    \"\"\"\n30\t\n31\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n32\t\n33\t    customer_id: CustomerId\n34\t    metric: Metric\n35\t    limit_per_window: LimitPerWindow\n36\t\n37\t\n38\tclass QuotaResponse(BaseModel):\n39\t    \"\"\"The minimal response field set for a quota (ASVS 15.3.1) — echoes only\n40\t    what the caller supplied, never the full `quotas` row (`api_key_id`,\n41\t    `created_at`, `updated_at` stay internal).\"\"\"\n42\t\n43\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n44\t\n45\t    customer_id: str\n46\t    metric: str\n47\t    limit_per_window: int\n48\t"}]},"uuid":"64bb5c51-e3a2-425c-a40f-f05c4de2434e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:26.077Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"774e28ff-098d-4e5e-b256-ca7d4dcca008","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"64bb5c51-e3a2-425c-a40f-f05c4de2434e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DJQaMhiR9Q7kJJhSAAwz8g","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\quota_service.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"aecb7a7b-0dc3-43f1-8931-a26bea13eabe","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:26.603Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"aecb7a7b-0dc3-43f1-8931-a26bea13eabe","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJQaMhiR9Q7kJJhSAAwz8g","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Service for `PUT /v1/quotas` — the admin-scoped upsert + 201/200 mapping.\n2\t\n3\tOrchestrates one transaction per request: the `xmax` upsert in\n4\t`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` reports create-vs-replace in a single\n5\tround-trip, so this layer only maps that to the HTTP status and emits the\n6\taudit-trail log (`quota.upsert`, plan §\"Repudiation\").\n7\t\"\"\"\n8\t\n9\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n10\t\n11\tfrom src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n12\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n13\tfrom src.db.session import scoped_transaction\n14\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n15\tfrom src.repositories.quotas_repo import upsert_quota\n16\t\n17\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n18\t\n19\t\n20\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n21\tclass QuotaUpsertOutcome:\n22\t    \"\"\"The result of processing a `PUT /v1/quotas` request: the stored quota\n23\t    and the HTTP status the route should return (201 create, 200 replace).\"\"\"\n24\t\n25\t    customer_id: str\n26\t    metric: str\n27\t    limit_per_window: int\n28\t    http_status: int\n29\t\n30\t\n31\tasync def upsert_tenant_quota(\n32\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal, payload: QuotaPutRequest\n33\t) -> QuotaUpsertOutcome:\n34\t    \"\"\"Create-or-replace the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the\n35\t    authenticated principal's own `api_key_id` — the server, never the\n36\t    client, sets `api_key_id`, which is the mass-assignment protection\n37\t    (ASVS 15.3.3) against writing another tenant's cap.\n38\t    \"\"\"\n39\t    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n40\t        record = await upsert_quota(\n41\t            session,\n42\t            api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n43\t            customer_id=payload.customer_id,\n44\t            metric=payload.metric,\n45\t            limit_per_window=payload.limit_per_window,\n46\t        )\n47\t\n48\t    action = \"create\" if record.inserted else \"replace\"\n49\t    logger.info(\n50\t        \"quota.upsert\",\n51\t        userId=principal.api_key_id,\n52\t        action=action,\n53\t        customer_id=record.customer_id,\n54\t        metric=record.metric,\n55\t        limit_per_window=record.limit_per_window,\n56\t    )\n57\t    return QuotaUpsertOutcome(\n58\t        customer_id=record.customer_id,\n59\t        metric=record.metric,\n60\t        limit_per_window=record.limit_per_window,\n61\t        http_status=201 if record.inserted else 200,\n62\t    )\n63\t\n64\t\n65\tdef to_response(outcome: QuotaUpsertOutcome) -> QuotaResponse:\n66\t    \"\"\"Map the service outcome to the minimal public response shape (ASVS 15.3.1).\"\"\"\n67\t    return QuotaResponse(\n68\t        customer_id=outcome.customer_id,\n69\t        metric=outcome.metric,\n70\t        limit_per_window=outcome.limit_per_window,\n71\t    )\n72\t"}]},"uuid":"a9b1f934-8311-43ec-93cb-d6492f59eda9","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:26.624Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"aecb7a7b-0dc3-43f1-8931-a26bea13eabe","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"a9b1f934-8311-43ec-93cb-d6492f59eda9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsK7n9n6vqUxSFm6Mp1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MXhqvdsDvctHswMS15KMdc","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\quotas_repo.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5450,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":728,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":5450,"output_tokens":728,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21553,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21553,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsK7kxqZHvHKus3v2U1p","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"6ae2773d-d816-4429-bf03-a5a962807d6c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:27.117Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"6ae2773d-d816-4429-bf03-a5a962807d6c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MXhqvdsDvctHswMS15KMdc","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Repository for `quotas` — the per-tenant, per-customer, per-metric usage\n2\tcap `upsert_quota` writes, and the atomic read-and-decide\n3\t`read_tenant_quota_state_locked` `POST /v1/events` consults.\n4\t\n5\tEvery query here is scoped by the authenticated `api_key_id` first (the\n6\trow-level-security invariant from `code-standards`); the PostgreSQL RLS\n7\tpolicy `quotas_tenant_isolation` is the backstop if this scoping were ever\n8\tmissing from a query.\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n12\tfrom datetime import datetime\n13\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n14\t\n15\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n16\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n17\t\n18\t\n19\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n20\tclass QuotaRecord:\n21\t    \"\"\"The stored/echoed shape of a `quotas` row plus whether this call\n22\t    created it (`inserted`) or replaced an existing cap.\"\"\"\n23\t\n24\t    customer_id: str\n25\t    metric: str\n26\t    limit_per_window: int\n27\t    inserted: bool\n28\t\n29\t\n30\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n31\tclass QuotaState:\n32\t    \"\"\"The result of the atomic read-and-decide: the configured cap and the\n33\t    current-window rollup total, read together under `FOR UPDATE OF q`.\"\"\"\n34\t\n35\t    limit_per_window: int\n36\t    current_total: Decimal\n37\t\n38\t\n39\tasync def upsert_quota(\n40\t    session: AsyncSession,\n41\t    *,\n42\t    api_key_id: int,\n43\t    customer_id: str,\n44\t    metric: str,\n45\t    limit_per_window: int,\n46\t) -> QuotaRecord:\n47\t    \"\"\"Create-or-replace the cap for `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)` in\n48\t    one statement, reporting whether this call inserted a new row.\n49\t\n50\t    `RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted` is the idiom that distinguishes a\n51\t    fresh `INSERT` from an `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` in a single round-trip: a\n52\t    freshly inserted row's `xmax` (the deleting-transaction marker) is still\n53\t    zero, while an updated row's `xmax` is set by the `UPDATE` — so the\n54\t    service can map `inserted -> 201` else `200` without a second read-before-\n55\t    write query or the TOCTOU race that would introduce.\n56\t    \"\"\"\n57\t    result = await session.execute(\n58\t        text(\n59\t            \"\"\"\n60\t            INSERT INTO quotas (api_key_id, customer_id, metric, limit_per_window, updated_at)\n61\t            VALUES (:api_key_id, :customer_id, :metric, :limit_per_window, now())\n62\t            ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE SET\n63\t                limit_per_window = EXCLUDED.limit_per_window,\n64\t                updated_at = now()\n65\t            RETURNING customer_id, metric, limit_per_window, (xmax = 0) AS inserted\n66\t            \"\"\"\n67\t        ),\n68\t        {\n69\t            \"api_key_id\": api_key_id,\n70\t            \"customer_id\": customer_id,\n71\t            \"metric\": metric,\n72\t            \"limit_per_window\": limit_per_window,\n73\t        },\n74\t    )\n75\t    row = result.mappings().one()\n76\t    return QuotaRecord(\n77\t        customer_id=row[\"customer_id\"],\n78\t        metric=row[\"metric\"],\n79\t        limit_per_window=row[\"limit_per_window\"],\n80\t        inserted=row[\"inserted\"],\n81\t    )\n82\t\n83\t\n84\tasync def read_tenant_quota_state_locked(\n85\t    session: AsyncSession,\n86\t    *,\n87\t    api_key_id: int,\n88\t    customer_id: str,\n89\t    metric: str,\n90\t    window_start: datetime,\n91\t) -> QuotaState | None:\n92\t    \"\"\"Lock the quota row, then read the current-window rollup total fresh —\n93\t    the atomic check-then-decide mechanism `POST /v1/events` uses to enforce\n94\t    `R + Q <= L` without a TOCTOU race (plan §\"The atomic read-and-decide\").\n95\t\n96\t    Returns None when no quota row matches `(api_key_id, customer_id,\n97\t    metric)` — the caller treats this as unlimited and takes no lock at all\n98\t    (the common, zero-contention path).\n99\t\n100\t    **Two round-trips, deliberately, not one combined `LEFT JOIN ... FOR\n101\t    UPDATE` statement.** `FOR UPDATE` only guarantees a fresh re-read of the\n102\t    *locked* row itself (via PostgreSQL's `EvalPlanQual` recheck) when a\n103\t    waiter unblocks after the lock holder commits — it does **not** force a\n104\t    fresh snapshot for other tables read in the same statement, including a\n105\t    `LEFT JOIN`. A waiter that queued for the lock before the holder\n106\t    committed would evaluate that join against its own original (pre-wait)\n107\t    snapshot and read a stale `total_quantity`, silently breaking strict\n108\t    enforcement under real concurrency (verified empirically: a single\n109\t    combined statement let every concurrent waiter read the same stale\n110\t    total and all get admitted). Issuing the `usage_rollup` read as its own\n111\t    statement *after* the lock is acquired gives it a fresh per-statement\n112\t    READ COMMITTED snapshot, which does include everything the previous lock\n113\t    holder just committed — this is what actually makes `current_total`\n114\t    accurate for every waiter, not just the first, uncontended caller.\n115\t    \"\"\"\n116\t    lock_result = await session.execute(\n117\t        text(\n118\t            \"\"\"\n119\t            SELECT limit_per_window\n120\t            FROM quotas\n121\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric\n122\t            FOR UPDATE\n123\t            \"\"\"\n124\t        ),\n125\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id, \"customer_id\": customer_id, \"metric\": metric},\n126\t    )\n127\t    lock_row = lock_result.mappings().first()\n128\t    if lock_row is None:\n129\t        return None\n130\t\n131\t    rollup_result = await session.execute(\n132\t        text(\n133\t            \"\"\"\n134\t            SELECT total_quantity\n135\t            FROM usage_rollup\n136\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id\n137\t              AND metric = :metric AND window_start = :window_start\n138\t            \"\"\"\n139\t        ),\n140\t        {\n141\t            \"api_key_id\": api_key_id,\n142\t            \"customer_id\": customer_id,\n143\t            \"metric\": metric,\n144\t            \"window_start\": window_start,\n145\t        },\n146\t    )\n147\t    rollup_row = rollup_result.mappings().first()\n148\t    current_total = rollup_row[\"total_quantity\"] if rollup_row is not None else Decimal(0)\n149\t    return QuotaState(limit_per_window=lock_row[\"limit_per_window\"], current_total=Decimal(current_total))\n150\t"}]},"uuid":"30cb6903-d6d2-49b9-93e7-17e0a4b3c00c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T22:59:27.139Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6ae2773d-d816-4429-bf03-a5a962807d6c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
