{"parentUuid":"fe5d4c28-9eaa-41a8-b2f8-2ed497a9b46b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WUSsMTJgqSFKhrFXWZXqVS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tfeature: usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\n3\tcriteria_total: 22\n4\tdelegated_criteria: [AC18]\n5\tderived_from: PROJECT.md + .pipeline/requirements.md (resolved items) + STRIDE + input-surface + DAST-readiness\n6\tnotes: >\n7\t  Feature-level definition-of-done. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a\n8\t  test (criteria_covered). AC18 is delegated to the security stage (ASVS reconciliation), so\n9\t  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\". No performance k6 load AC: the export is\n10\t  a reporting route with a documented p95 sanity check (AC16); the binding perf constraint is the\n11\t  negative one (AC15 — existing endpoints/budgets untouched). AC22 (added in the revision pass)\n12\t  covers the pre-flight safe-error shape — distinct from plan §R3, which only accepts the\n13\t  post-200 mid-stream truncation case.\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n17\t|---|---|---|---|\n18\t| AC1 | Response is RFC 4180 CSV via stdlib `csv`: header row exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief column order), CRLF line endings, fields containing comma/quote/newline quoted | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit (dialect, header, CRLF, quoting) + integration end-to-end body assertion |\n19\t| AC2 | Optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters applied (reusing existing allowlist types + window bounds); all omitted → full supported range | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Unit (schema) + integration (each filter narrows the row set; none → all caller rows) |\n20\t| AC3 | `from`/`to` validation: timezone-aware, `from <= to`, both within `[now-90d, now+1h]`, naive datetime rejected | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py` | Unit (accept/reject cases incl. naive, inverted range, out-of-window) |\n21\t| AC4 | Input validation (non-waivable): malformed / wrong-type / unknown / out-of-range query param → 422 `validation_failed`; `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects unknown params | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | Unit + integration (422 envelope with `code=validation_failed`) |\n22\t| AC5 | Rate limit: post-auth **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** throttle applies (principal-keyed); two principals on one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | Integration two-principals-one-IP discriminating test |\n23\t| AC6 | Authorization: any authenticated key (ingest or admin) may export; unauthenticated/invalid → 401; no scope gate | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/auth` | Integration (ingest key 200, admin key 200, no/invalid key 401) |\n24\t| AC7 | Tenant isolation: export returns ONLY the caller's `api_key_id` rows; two tenants' data never cross (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; RLS is backstop) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration two-tenant test (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) |\n25\t| AC8 | Row cap: a result exceeding 100,000 rows → 422 `validation_failed` (\"narrow filters\"), **no partial body streamed** (pre-flight count before any response byte) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (>100k rows → 422, response body is the envelope not CSV) |\n26\t| AC9 | Streaming constant memory: rows streamed as read via a server-side cursor, response not fully buffered before send | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration streaming-not-buffered sanity (first bytes observable before generator exhausted / bounded memory on a large export) |\n27\t| AC10 | CSV formula-injection escape: text cells (`customer_id`,`metric`) starting with `= + - @ \\t \\r` prefixed with `'`; control chars neutralized; numeric/timestamp cells untouched | `src/api/csv_export.py` | Unit (incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, each trigger, control chars, numeric/timestamp unaffected) + integration end-to-end |\n28\t| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n29\t| AC12 | Empty result → 200 header-only CSV (single header row, zero data rows), never 404 | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration (caller with no matching rollups → 200, one CSV line) |\n30\t| AC13 | Deterministic ordering `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC`; identical exports are byte-stable | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (asserts row order over a seeded multi-row set) |\n31\t| AC14 | Value formats: `window_start` as UTC ISO-8601 with offset (identical to JSON response form); `total_quantity` as `str(Decimal)` (plain decimal, no scientific notation) | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit + integration (format assertions) |\n32\t| AC15 | No behavior change: `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, `PUT /v1/quotas` behavior/budgets/tests unchanged; no new Alembic revision / migration added | repo-wide (negative) | Existing test suites pass unchanged; no new file under `alembic/versions/` |\n33\t| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 <= 3,000 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC). *[Human-confirmed at the 2026-07-09 debugging escalation, resolving plan Open Q1: the proposed 500 ms is unreachable within the approved constant-memory streaming design (irreducible ~0.85–1.0 s cursor+encoding floor; optimized p95 2.07 s stable at the cap). 500 ms would require a design change (buffered fetch or lower cap) and is recorded as aspiration, not budget.]* | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows asserting the <= 3,000 ms bound |\n34\t| AC17 | Audit logging: exactly one `usage.export` `info` event at completion (`userId`=opaque `api_key_id`, `operation`, `rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — no raw `customer_id`); over-cap request logged at `warn` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/logging` | Unit/integration (log fields present, no PII, one event; `warn` on over-cap) |\n35\t| AC18 | ASVS 5.0 L1/L2 controls for the triggered chapters (V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V13/V14/V16) present across the change set; recorded waivers honored | cross-cutting | Delegated to security stage (`delegated:\"security\"`) — reconciled against plan §ASVS Compliance |\n36\t| AC19 (DAST-1) | Served OpenAPI schema includes `GET /v1/usage/export` with its `200 text/csv` and `422` responses, matching the implemented route (not hand-drifted) | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Integration (assert route + responses present in `/openapi.json`) |\n37\t| AC20 (DAST-2) | A seeded non-production DAST test key (reuse the existing seeded key; credentials from env/secrets, never hardcoded) can call the export | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` (existing), test fixtures | Integration (seeded key successfully hits the export in staging/local) |\n38\t| AC21 (DAST-3) | Auth-context recorded for scanners: `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` header shape, documented in the plan and exercised by the integration auth path | plan §Auth, `src/auth/api_key.py` (existing) | Documented in plan + integration test uses this exact Bearer shape |\n39\t| AC22 | Safe-error / fail-closed pre-flight: a forced internal error during the pre-flight `prepare_export` `COUNT` phase (before any response byte) returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (no stack/SQL/internal path leaked), rolls back the transaction, and starts **no** stream / emits **no** partial CSV body (ASVS 16.5.x). Distinct from plan §R3 (post-200 mid-stream truncation, accepted) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py`, `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Unit in `tests/test_usage_export_service.py` (non-cap DB error propagates, not swallowed, no stream started) + integration in `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (forced pre-flight `COUNT` error → `500 internal` envelope, no leak, no partial body) |\n40\t"}]},"uuid":"8065b00f-ced1-43f6-a91d-c179c82c483c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:00:08.881Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"fe5d4c28-9eaa-41a8-b2f8-2ed497a9b46b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"8065b00f-ced1-43f6-a91d-c179c82c483c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsKB2qQHNHXG9fDEBN4P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016bLA4u1tY25qs5tAs9HDRM","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\logging\\__init__.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2005,"cache_read_input_tokens":62862,"output_tokens":441,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2005},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":441,"cache_read_input_tokens":62862,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2005,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2005,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsKB1QLRkDKybgtXU4oq","attributionAgent":"planning","attributionSkill":"pipeline-orchestration","type":"assistant","uuid":"bc09e1ea-a761-4922-b878-734f946621bc","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:00:09.410Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"bc09e1ea-a761-4922-b878-734f946621bc","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016bLA4u1tY25qs5tAs9HDRM","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Structured logging facade — `get_logger()` is the only way application code\n2\tshould obtain a logger.\n3\t\n4\tConfigures structlog once at import time to emit JSON to stdout (ECS ships\n5\tstdout to CloudWatch with no further app change) and applies a centralized\n6\tredaction processor so a secret or raw PII value can never leave the process\n7\tthrough a log line, regardless of which call site logs it.\n8\t\"\"\"\n9\t\n10\timport logging as stdlib_logging\n11\timport sys\n12\tfrom typing import Any\n13\t\n14\timport structlog\n15\t\n16\t_REDACTED = \"***redacted***\"\n17\t\n18\t# Field names that must never appear in raw form in a log event — the API-key\n19\t# secret/Authorization header and any raw customer identifier (personal data\n20\t# class per data-protection-conventions). Matched case-insensitively against\n21\t# structlog event-dict keys.\n22\t_SENSITIVE_KEYS = frozenset(\n23\t    {\n24\t        \"authorization\",\n25\t        \"api_key\",\n26\t        \"api_key_secret\",\n27\t        \"secret\",\n28\t        \"secret_hash\",\n29\t        \"password\",\n30\t        \"customer_id\",\n31\t        \"token\",\n32\t    }\n33\t)\n34\t\n35\t\n36\tdef _redact_sensitive_fields(\n37\t    _logger: Any, _method_name: str, event_dict: dict[str, Any]\n38\t) -> dict[str, Any]:\n39\t    \"\"\"Strip sensitive values from a structlog event dict before it is rendered.\n40\t\n41\t    This is the centralized PII/secret-redaction control every log call\n42\t    inherits automatically — call sites never redact ad hoc.\n43\t    \"\"\"\n44\t    for key in list(event_dict.keys()):\n45\t        if key.lower() in _SENSITIVE_KEYS:\n46\t            event_dict[key] = _REDACTED\n47\t    return event_dict\n48\t\n49\t\n50\tdef _strip_control_characters(\n51\t    _logger: Any, _method_name: str, event_dict: dict[str, Any]\n52\t) -> dict[str, Any]:\n53\t    \"\"\"Neutralize newlines/control characters in string values to prevent log forging.\"\"\"\n54\t    for key, value in event_dict.items():\n55\t        if isinstance(value, str):\n56\t            event_dict[key] = value.replace(\"\\r\", \"\\\\r\").replace(\"\\n\", \"\\\\n\")\n57\t    return event_dict\n58\t\n59\t\n60\tdef _configure_structlog() -> None:\n61\t    \"\"\"Configure structlog once at import time: JSON renderer, ISO timestamps,\n62\t    the redaction/anti-forging processors, and stdlib logging routed through it.\"\"\"\n63\t    stdlib_logging.basicConfig(\n64\t        format=\"%(message)s\", stream=sys.stdout, level=stdlib_logging.INFO\n65\t    )\n66\t    structlog.configure(\n67\t        processors=[\n68\t            structlog.contextvars.merge_contextvars,\n69\t            structlog.processors.add_log_level,\n70\t            structlog.processors.TimeStamper(fmt=\"iso\", utc=True, key=\"timestamp\"),\n71\t            _redact_sensitive_fields,\n72\t            _strip_control_characters,\n73\t            structlog.processors.StackInfoRenderer(),\n74\t            structlog.processors.format_exc_info,\n75\t            structlog.processors.JSONRenderer(),\n76\t        ],\n77\t        wrapper_class=structlog.make_filtering_bound_logger(stdlib_logging.INFO),\n78\t        context_class=dict,\n79\t        logger_factory=structlog.PrintLoggerFactory(),\n80\t        cache_logger_on_first_use=True,\n81\t    )\n82\t\n83\t\n84\t_configure_structlog()\n85\t\n86\t\n87\tdef get_logger(**initial_values: Any) -> structlog.stdlib.BoundLogger:\n88\t    \"\"\"Return the single configured structlog logger, optionally bound with\n89\t    initial context values (e.g. `service=...`).\n90\t\n91\t    Every module imports this rather than instantiating its own logger, so\n92\t    redaction and field conventions stay centralized (`code-standards` facade\n93\t    rule).\n94\t    \"\"\"\n95\t    return structlog.get_logger(**initial_values)\n96\t"}]},"uuid":"865ad1bb-573a-4da9-9bcc-e5f22073f03d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:00:09.425Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bc09e1ea-a761-4922-b878-734f946621bc","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
