{"parentUuid":"c0c4885e-8efa-43f6-9fa5-37721aded370","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsL7fNbufjr9LqPqrL19","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QeTgxqeFuwveEqCmkk2Dif","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\plan-audit.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7801,"cache_read_input_tokens":134405,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7801,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsL7eBfTYZXeAphpETpB","attributionAgent":"planning","type":"assistant","uuid":"d3f4996b-e8f6-4715-821d-c750c1128862","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:12:30.671Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"d3f4996b-e8f6-4715-821d-c750c1128862","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QeTgxqeFuwveEqCmkk2Dif","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\taudited_at: 2026-07-09T00:00:00Z\n3\tplan_sha256: f84c89d434d6aa6e6a485cd68d84d0a64e42a8eb3c068f6af78cceab147732c\n4\tflags_total: 1\n5\tmaterial_flags: 1\n6\tcritical_flags: 0\n7\trevision_recommended: true\n8\tdependencies_checked: 0\n9\tdependencies_unverified: 0\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\t## Focus here first\n13\t\n14\t- **[material]** No safe-error-handling (ASVS-DET T2-2) acceptance criterion for `GET`/`DELETE\n15\t  /v1/quotas`. Both handlers do live DB I/O (`SELECT`, `DELETE … RETURNING`) that can raise\n16\t  server-side, and this exact project already has the precedent test shape for it —\n17\t  `tests/integration/test_events_endpoint.py::test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed`\n18\t  (feature 1's AC19). `acceptance.md` for this feature has no equivalent criterion, and `plan.md`\n19\t  never states an N/A rationale for omitting it. Without it, a forced DB exception on GET/DELETE\n20\t  is unverified: it could leak a stack trace/SQL fragment or leave inconsistent state, and nothing\n21\t  in the 18-criterion set would catch it. This is otherwise a very tight, well-reasoned plan —\n22\t  everything else audited clean.\n23\t\n24\tNo other blocking concerns — completeness, ambiguity, proof-claim, and dependency dimensions all\n25\tread clean; see detail below.\n26\t\n27\t## Completeness\n28\t\n29\t| Dimension | Status | Missing item | Blocks which agent | material/advisory |\n30\t|---|---|---|---|---|\n31\t| Layer sections present | ✓ | — (Frontend correctly omitted: `design source: none`, backend-only API) | — | — |\n32\t| Acceptance criteria traced | ✓ | Every `requirements.md` Resolved item and `CLAUDE.md`/`PROJECT.md` \"what done means\" line traces to a named plan section and/or `acceptance.md` ID (AC1–AC18) | — | — |\n33\t| Task decomposition (`tasks.md`) | N/A | Correctly absent — 7-file change set is below the ≥8-file / ≥25-file / ≥15-criteria threshold | — | — |\n34\t| STRIDE mechanisms named | ✓ | Every threat row names a concrete mechanism + file (e.g. `constr` allowlist in `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, FORCE RLS in `alembic/versions/0003_*`) | — | — |\n35\t| Input-surface controls | ✓ | GET (no params, N/A validation + AC12 rate-limit) and DELETE (AC9 validation, non-waivable + AC12 rate-limit, principal-keyed post-auth Tier-2 — correctly not IP-keyed) both fully accounted for | — | — |\n36\t| Data-protection | ✓ | No stored field; explicit `data_protection_waiver` given in plan + `acceptance.md` frontmatter, reasoned (RDS SSE, non-sensitive class) | — | — |\n37\t| Object-level authorization tested | ✓ | AC8 (DELETE cross-tenant → 404, victim row intact) + AC2 (GET tenant isolation) | — | — |\n38\t| Authentication boundary tested | ✓ | AC5 (GET 401), AC11 (DELETE 401) | — | — |\n39\t| **Safe-error handling tested** | **gap** | No `acceptance.md` criterion for a forced internal error on GET/DELETE returning the generic envelope + failing closed (ASVS-DET T2-2); project precedent exists (`test_events_endpoint.py::test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed`, AC19) | security (`security_surface` reconciliation) and testing (nothing to write against) | **material** |\n40\t| Security-property tests (T2-3…T2-6) | N/A | No self-contained tokens, no sessions, no multi-write/ledger op, no password path — none of the four triggers apply | — | — |\n41\t| App-store submission criteria | N/A | No app-store target declared | — | — |\n42\t| DAST readiness | ✓ | AC17 covers DAST-1 (served OpenAPI, both verbs) and DAST-2/3 (seeded admin test key + `mtr_live`/`Bearer` auth context) | — | — |\n43\t| ASVS compliance scoped | ✓ | `## ASVS Compliance` block present: triggered chapters, in-scope L3 (V8.2.x, justified), waivers stated (none for L1/L2) | — | — |\n44\t| Test strategy declared | ✓ | `pyramid`, project default, with rationale for the integration-tier bias toward Postgres-only guarantees | — | — |\n45\t| Files affected concrete | ✓ | 6 modified + 1 created source/test file, each with a one-line reason; docs deferred to documentation stage per convention | — | — |\n46\t| Repomix receipt | N/A | `.pipeline/repomix-pack.xml` not present — check skipped per instructions | — | — |\n47\t\n48\t## Ambiguities\n49\t\n50\tNone found. The plan is unusually precise for a small brownfield increment: every endpoint has\n51\tverb + path + status codes, every field has a type/validator, no undefined referents, no\n52\t`TODO`/`TBD`/placeholder markers, no internal contradictions between sections (Stack notes, Data,\n53\tAuth, Files affected all agree: no migration, no new dependency, same admin gate). The two **Open\n54\tquestions** (GET read-logging, ordering collation) are exactly the kind of deferred-with-a-\n55\tproposed-default items the plan process expects — each states its default and asks the checkpoint\n56\tto confirm, not a gap.\n57\t\n58\t## Proof-claim verification (U-03)\n59\t\n60\tScanned for `provably/guaranteed/invariant/cannot happen/always .../by construction`-shaped\n61\tassertions. Three found, all traced to an enforcement point:\n62\t- \"deterministic `ORDER BY customer_id, metric`\" → enforced by `ORDER BY` itself and proven by\n63\t  `test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields` (AC1).\n64\t- \"the facade guarantees\" `customer_id` redaction in logs → enforced by the structlog facade and\n65\t  proven by `test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged` (AC16, asserts redaction in `capsys`).\n66\t- \"a cross-tenant DELETE matches zero rows → 404\" (repeated in the STRIDE table, diagram caption,\n67\t  and copy-paste prompt) → enforced by the `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS policy (`0003`) and\n68\t  proven by `test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant` (AC8, asserts both A→404 and B's row intact).\n69\tNo unenforced invariant claims found.\n70\t\n71\t## Cross-feature data-flow trace (U-03)\n72\t\n73\tNot triggered in the risky sense: this feature reads/deletes rows written by the *same* admin\n74\tprincipal (`api_key_id`) via the sibling `PUT /v1/quotas` in the same quota-admin surface — there\n75\tis no different reading principal or reader/writer key mismatch of the feature-3 shape. No bridge\n76\tissue to flag.\n77\t\n78\t## Dependency reality\n79\t\n80\tNo new dependencies. `pyproject.toml` is unchanged by this plan — every module touched\n81\t(`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`,\n82\t`src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`) is an existing first-party module extended\n83\twith new functions/handlers reusing already-pinned libraries (FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Pydantic). The\n84\t`dependency-audit-policy` skill was not invoked.\n85\t\n86\t## Version policy\n87\t\n88\tNo new dependencies — nothing to evaluate.\n89\t\n90\t## Could not verify\n91\t\n92\tNothing — no registry lookups were needed (no new dependencies).\n93\t"}]},"uuid":"965e0614-bafe-45a4-ade4-3693520fb10a","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:12:30.686Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d3f4996b-e8f6-4715-821d-c750c1128862","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"965e0614-bafe-45a4-ade4-3693520fb10a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsL7fNbufjr9LqPqrL19","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Jz4tMX7voxdSuEoKPuUDEZ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_events_endpoint.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7801,"cache_read_input_tokens":134405,"output_tokens":414,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7801},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":414,"cache_read_input_tokens":134405,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7801,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7801,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsL7eBfTYZXeAphpETpB","attributionAgent":"planning","type":"assistant","uuid":"028d4720-d418-4a77-b41f-783ff8b1783e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:12:30.992Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"028d4720-d418-4a77-b41f-783ff8b1783e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"895b7771-0494-4fd1-9c42-d5085f2ef142","agentId":"a0fbc342a4e25e60d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jz4tMX7voxdSuEoKPuUDEZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Integration tests for `POST /v1/events` against a real Postgres + Redis\n2\t(AC1, AC2, AC3, AC13-wire, AC18, AC19).\"\"\"\n3\t\n4\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n5\t\n6\timport pytest\n7\tfrom httpx import ASGITransport, AsyncClient\n8\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n9\t\n10\t\n11\tdef _payload(**overrides) -> dict:\n12\t    payload = {\n13\t        \"customer_id\": \"cust_1\",\n14\t        \"metric\": \"api_calls\",\n15\t        \"quantity\": \"5\",\n16\t        \"idempotency_key\": \"idem-key-1\",\n17\t    }\n18\t    payload.update(overrides)\n19\t    return payload\n20\t\n21\t\n22\tasync def test_post_event_returns_201_and_persists_one_row(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n23\t    \"\"\"AC1: valid key + body -> 201, exactly one `events` row, minimal response fields.\"\"\"\n24\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key()\n25\t\n26\t    response = await client.post(\n27\t        \"/v1/events\",\n28\t        json=_payload(),\n29\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"},\n30\t    )\n31\t\n32\t    assert response.status_code == 201\n33\t    body = response.json()\n34\t    assert set(body.keys()) == {\"event_id\", \"customer_id\", \"metric\", \"quantity\", \"window_start\", \"idempotent_replay\"}\n35\t    assert body[\"idempotent_replay\"] is False\n36\t    assert body[\"customer_id\"] == \"cust_1\"\n37\t    assert Decimal(str(body[\"quantity\"])) == Decimal(\"5\")\n38\t\n39\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n40\t\n41\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n42\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n43\t        count = (await connection.execute(text(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM events WHERE api_key_id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id})).scalar_one()\n44\t    await engine.dispose()\n45\t    assert count == 1\n46\t\n47\t\n48\tasync def test_duplicate_idempotency_key_is_a_no_op(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n49\t    \"\"\"AC2: a replayed idempotency_key creates no new row and does not double-increment the rollup.\"\"\"\n50\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key()\n51\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n52\t\n53\t    first = await client.post(\"/v1/events\", json=_payload(), headers=headers)\n54\t    assert first.status_code == 201\n55\t\n56\t    second = await client.post(\"/v1/events\", json=_payload(quantity=\"999\"), headers=headers)\n57\t    assert second.status_code == 200\n58\t    assert second.json()[\"idempotent_replay\"] is True\n59\t\n60\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n61\t\n62\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n63\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n64\t        event_count = (\n65\t            await connection.execute(text(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM events WHERE api_key_id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id})\n66\t        ).scalar_one()\n67\t        rollup_row = (\n68\t            await connection.execute(\n69\t                text(\n70\t                    \"SELECT total_quantity, event_count FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id\"\n71\t                ),\n72\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n73\t            )\n74\t        ).mappings().first()\n75\t    await engine.dispose()\n76\t\n77\t    assert event_count == 1\n78\t    assert rollup_row[\"event_count\"] == 1\n79\t    assert Decimal(rollup_row[\"total_quantity\"]) == Decimal(\"5\")\n80\t\n81\t\n82\tasync def test_replay_body_pins_the_original_event_representation(client, make_api_key):\n83\t    \"\"\"AC3: the replay response equals the *original* event, not the duplicate's payload,\n84\t    even when the duplicate carries different values (replay semantics pinned).\"\"\"\n85\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key()\n86\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n87\t\n88\t    first = await client.post(\"/v1/events\", json=_payload(quantity=\"5\"), headers=headers)\n89\t    first_body = first.json()\n90\t\n91\t    second = await client.post(\n92\t        \"/v1/events\",\n93\t        json=_payload(quantity=\"9999\", customer_id=\"cust_1\"),\n94\t        headers=headers,\n95\t    )\n96\t    second_body = second.json()\n97\t\n98\t    assert second_body[\"event_id\"] == first_body[\"event_id\"]\n99\t    assert Decimal(str(second_body[\"quantity\"])) == Decimal(str(first_body[\"quantity\"])) == Decimal(\"5\")\n100\t    assert second_body[\"idempotent_replay\"] is True\n101\t    assert first_body[\"idempotent_replay\"] is False\n102\t\n103\t\n104\tasync def test_injection_payload_in_customer_id_is_rejected_at_the_boundary(client, make_api_key):\n105\t    \"\"\"AC13-wire: an injection payload never reaches the SQL sink — 422 at the schema boundary.\"\"\"\n106\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key()\n107\t    response = await client.post(\n108\t        \"/v1/events\",\n109\t        json=_payload(customer_id=\"' OR 1=1--\"),\n110\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"},\n111\t    )\n112\t    assert response.status_code == 422\n113\t\n114\t\n115\tasync def test_wrong_secret_for_a_known_key_id_is_rejected(client, make_api_key):\n116\t    \"\"\"AC18: a well-formed token with a valid key_id but the wrong secret is\n117\t    denied (401), indistinguishable from an unknown key_id.\"\"\"\n118\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key()\n119\t    key_id = presented_key.split(\"_\")[2]\n120\t    tampered_key = f\"mtr_live_{key_id}_{'0' * 32}\"\n121\t\n122\t    response = await client.post(\n123\t        \"/v1/events\",\n124\t        json=_payload(),\n125\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {tampered_key}\"},\n126\t    )\n127\t    assert response.status_code == 401\n128\t\n129\t\n130\tasync def test_revoked_api_key_is_rejected(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n131\t    \"\"\"AC18: a revoked key is denied (401), never 200.\"\"\"\n132\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key()\n133\t\n134\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n135\t\n136\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n137\t    async with engine.begin() as connection:\n138\t        await connection.execute(\n139\t            text(\"UPDATE api_keys SET revoked_at = now() WHERE id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id}\n140\t        )\n141\t    await engine.dispose()\n142\t\n143\t    response = await client.post(\n144\t        \"/v1/events\",\n145\t        json=_payload(),\n146\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"},\n147\t    )\n148\t    assert response.status_code == 401\n149\t\n150\t\n151\tasync def test_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed(\n152\t    truncate_tables, make_api_key, postgres_url, monkeypatch\n153\t):\n154\t    \"\"\"AC19: a forced internal error returns the generic envelope (no stack/SQL leak)\n155\t    and leaves no partial write behind (event + rollup are one transaction).\"\"\"\n156\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key()\n157\t\n158\t    from src.services import events_service\n159\t\n160\t    async def _boom(*args, **kwargs):\n161\t        raise RuntimeError(\"simulated failure mid-write\")\n162\t\n163\t    monkeypatch.setattr(events_service, \"increment_usage_rollup\", _boom)\n164\t\n165\t    # ASGITransport re-raises app exceptions by default (useful for debugging\n166\t    # a broken test); here we're deliberately exercising the app's own 500\n167\t    # handler, so this client must let it convert the exception to a response.\n168\t    from src.main import app\n169\t\n170\t    transport = ASGITransport(app=app, raise_app_exceptions=False)\n171\t    async with AsyncClient(transport=transport, base_url=\"http://test\") as client:\n172\t        response = await client.post(\n173\t            \"/v1/events\",\n174\t            json=_payload(idempotency_key=\"will-fail\"),\n175\t            headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"},\n176\t        )\n177\t\n178\t    assert response.status_code == 500\n179\t    body = response.json()\n180\t    assert body[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"internal\"\n181\t    assert \"requestId\" in body[\"error\"]\n182\t    message = body[\"error\"][\"message\"].lower()\n183\t    assert \"runtimeerror\" not in message\n184\t    assert \"simulated failure\" not in message\n185\t    assert \"traceback\" not in message\n186\t\n187\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n188\t\n189\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n190\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n191\t        event_count = (\n192\t            await connection.execute(\n193\t                text(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM events WHERE api_key_id = :id AND idempotency_key = 'will-fail'\"),\n194\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n195\t            )\n196\t        ).scalar_one()\n197\t    await engine.dispose()\n198\t    assert event_count == 0, \"the failed transaction must not leave a partial event row\"\n199\t"}]},"uuid":"592e45e4-8f5a-4724-ade9-b4fa8d313653","timestamp":"2026-07-09T23:12:30.998Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"028d4720-d418-4a77-b41f-783ff8b1783e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
